news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement posts net loss of Rs 19.24 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,242.67 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 21.77 per cent from Rs 1,588.51 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance's net profit up 15.31% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Aadhar Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 764.28 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 21.57 per cent from Rs 628.67 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: NGT forms panel to investigate illegal sand mining on Son river in Bihar
news.para: The green body was hearing a plea claiming unauthorised mining in the river by construction of temporary dams in Amiyavar's block Nasirganj village to Tilouthu which obstructed the river's flow besides damaging the waterbody's flora and fauna.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto surge 14% in October 2024
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales increased 14% in October following a modest rise of 3.3% in September, according to Toronto Regional Real Estate Board data.

news.title: TARC posts net loss of Rs 67.36 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: TARC's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 5.02 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 85.52 per cent from Rs 34.67 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to issue fresh tenders for Amaravati development work
news.para: ​​Between 2014 and 2019, he noted that tenders worth Rs 41,000 crore were called for Amaravati development and works to the tune of Rs 35,000 crore were also taken up.

news.title: Delhi mandates heaters for night-duty workers at construction sites over 500 sq metres
news.para: He said that apart from resident welfare associations, construction sites that are over 500 square metres in area will have to provide heaters to night-time workers and security guards.

news.title: Police intensifies measures to check diversion of free sand in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: ​​Allegations have emerged that brokers have been diverting free sand, meant for public use to neighbouring states, to earn profit. This has prompted for an intensified response from law enforcement.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM inaugurates new IT park in Vilankurichi
news.para: Spread over an area of 2.94 lakh sq ft and constructed at a cost of Rs 158.32 crore, the new IT park is expected to provide employment opportunities to 3,500 people.

news.title: Hi Tech Pipes' net profit remains flat in Q2 FY25
news.para: Hi Tech Pipes' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 706.86 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 18.52 per cent from Rs 867.50 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kanpur falls behind in smart city rank, relegates to B category
news.para: During the state government's review meeting, the status of various ongoing projects under Smart City, Kanpur was deemed unsatisfactory, resulting in the city receiving 8 out of 10 marks in September. This relegated it to smart city B category.

news.title: Indore administration launches crackdown on illegal colonies, 100 cases identified
news.para: The senior administrative official said that fair chances are being given to the colonisers to present all the permissions along with legal documents of the land on which they developed the colonies.

news.title: CapitaLand Investment raises S$131 million from Daibiru Corporation for its CIG Fund 2
news.para: Daibiru Corporation is a real estate subsidiary of Mitsui O.S.K. Lines in Japan. The capital commitment will increase CIGF2’s FUM to more than S$1 billion.

news.title: Lucknow development body sells 86 flats in 15 days
news.para: This limited-time offer, available from Oct 21 to Dec 31, provides additional discounts on flats, ranging from Rs1 lakh to Rs 2.5 lakh.

news.title: Bombay HC criticizes BMC over delay in repairs of South Mumbai’s Dwarka building
news.para: In July 2023, BMC's technical advisory committee categorised the 100-year-old building as C 2-A category - partially unsafe/dangerous requiring major structural repairs. Since the landlord took no steps, in Oct 2023 the petitioners moved HC.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA grants permits to over 200 projects after water source verification
news.para: Both Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) and Pimpri-Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) had expressed their inability last month to supply water to areas beyond 5km of their jurisdiction.

news.title: Court appoints new directors of Oberoi Hotels & Oberoi Properties amid inheritance dispute
news.para: The appointments were confirmed during an annual general meeting on Tuesday, people said. The appointments were made abiding by terms of a consent order passed by the Delhi High Court earlier in the day.

news.title: Bengaluru metro's extended green line operation may launch from November 6
news.para: Chief PRO of BMRCL said, "We are working on fixing train schedules and deploying staff at the three new stations. We will share details on operating trains till Madavara on Wednesday."

news.title: Telangana RERA imposes Rs 15 lakh penalty on Jayabheri Properties
news.para: The complainants claimed ownership of approximately 28 acres of land in Puppalaguda village in Gandipet mandal in Rangareddy District. They filed suits for a declaration of title, which is pending before the III additional district judge, Rangareddy, LB Nagar.
